      • queryAfterRemoval

        @Nullable
public java.lang.String queryAfterRemoval
        The markup text indicating which parts of the original query have been removed in order to retrieve a non-empty result set. The removed parts are surrounded by <em></em> tags.

        Note: Only returned when removeWordsIfNoResults is true.

      • aroundLatLng

        @Nullable
public com.algolia.search.saas.AbstractQuery.LatLng aroundLatLng
        The computed geo location.

        Note: Only returned when aroundLatLngViaIp is true.

      • automaticRadius

        @Nullable
public java.lang.Integer automaticRadius
        The automatically computed radius.

        Note: Only returned for geo queries without an explicitly specified radius (see Query.setAroundRadius(java.lang.Integer)).

      • serverUsed

        public java.lang.String serverUsed
        Actual host name of the server that processed the request. (Our DNS supports automatic failover and load balancing, so this may differ from the host name used in the request.)

        Note: Only returned when getRankingInfo is true.

      • parsedQuery

        public java.lang.String parsedQuery
        The query string that will be searched, after normalization.

        Note: Only returned when getRankingInfo is true.

      • timeoutCounts

        public java.lang.Boolean timeoutCounts
        Whether a timeout was hit when computing the facet counts. When true, the counts will be interpolated (i.e. approximate). See also exhaustiveFacetsCount.

        Note: Only returned when getRankingInfo is true.

      • timeoutHits

        public java.lang.Boolean timeoutHits
        Whether a timeout was hit when retrieving the hits. When true, some results may be missing.

        Note: Only returned when getRankingInfo is true.
